          <p>Often called the "underrated Grey," the Timneh is smaller and darker than the Congo — 275–375 grams, a charcoal-grey body, a deep maroon tail, and a distinctive horn-colored patch on the upper beak. Anyone weighing a <a href="/congo-african-grey-for-sale/" class="text-clay font-medium underline decoration-clay/30 hover:decoration-clay">Congo African Grey against a Timneh</a> is really choosing between two temperaments, not two levels of intelligence.</p>
