    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 pb-12">
      <h3 class="font-lora font-bold text-2xl text-logo-dark mb-3 mt-2">What a healthy African Grey looks like</h3>
      <p class="text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4" style="max-width:70ch;">A healthy Grey is bright-eyed and alert, with smooth, tight feathering and a clean vent. It perches confidently on both feet, has a strong grip, eats and drinks normally, and produces well-formed droppings. Its breathing is silent and effortless — no tail-bobbing at rest, no clicking or wheezing. Every bird we ship has been examined by an avian veterinarian and cleared on exactly these points, with the certificate dated within 10 days of travel.</p>
      <h3 class="font-lora font-bold text-2xl text-logo-dark mb-3">Common conditions, explained (and how we guard against them)</h3>
      <div class="space-y-3 text-stone-600 leading-relaxed" style="max-width:70ch;">
        <p><strong>PBFD (psittacine beak and feather disease)</strong> is a viral disease that damages feathers and the immune system. It is one of the most important reasons to buy from a documented, closed-aviary breeder rather than a swap meet or anonymous seller — our birds are raised in a controlled environment and vet-screened before placement.</p>
        <p><strong>Psittacosis</strong> (parrot fever) is a bacterial infection that can affect birds and, rarely, people. A vet-checked, captive-bred bird from a clean aviary is the single best protection, and our health certificate confirms a clear exam before travel.</p>
        <p><strong>Hypocalcemia (calcium deficiency)</strong> is a condition African Greys are specifically prone to. We start every chick on a calcium-supported, pellet-based diet with fresh vegetables and send that diet plan home with you so the transition never triggers a deficiency.</p>
        <p><strong>Feather-plucking</strong> is almost always behavioral, not medical — a sign of boredom, stress, or too little interaction. It is preventable with the enrichment and daily engagement we coach every new owner through. This is why our support doesn't end at pickup.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
